                        new
                        {
                            Id = 9L,
                            Description = "A theologian, probably a Jesuit, reads and comments on the council decisions. His secular secretary notes. On the left is the lectern, decorated with a sculpture of a Calvary group, and with part 36 of the collected council decrees on it. On the right a work table with a richly coloured tablecloth, on which the priest and the secretary are seated. On the table there are study attributes, such as a globe and a book. Behind it is a bookcase with biblical editions and literature in the field of theology, exegesis and ecclesiastical law. In the upper left corner is the age of the theologian: 'Aetatis 47' (at the age of 47). As is often the case, Van Oost is again inspired by the portraits of Anthony van Dyck. ",
